#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.31"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.31:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.31:0.2"
msgid "4. Sumanavagga"
msgstr "4. With Sumanā"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.31:0.3"
msgid "31. Sumanasutta"
msgstr "31. With Sumanā"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.31:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ … pe … anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "an5.31:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sumanā rājakumārī pañcahi rathasatehi pañcahi rājakumārisatehi "
"parivutā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā "
"ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho sumanā rājakumārī bhagavantaṃ "
"etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Princess Sumanā, escorted by five hundred chariots and five hundred "
"royal maidens, went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said "
"to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.33"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.31:2.1"
msgid "“Idhassu, bhante, bhagavato dve sāvakā samasaddhā samasīlā samapaññā—"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, suppose there were two disciples equal in faith, ethics, and wisdom."

msgctxt "an5.31:2.2"
msgid "eko dāyako, eko adāyako."
msgstr "One is a giver, one is not."

msgctxt "an5.31:2.3"
msgid "Te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a "
"heavenly realm."

#. VAR: nesaṃ → tesaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an5.31:2.4"
msgid "Devabhūtānaṃ pana nesaṃ, bhante, siyā viseso, siyā nānākaraṇan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"When they have become gods, would there be any distinction or difference "
"between them?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an5.31:3.1"
msgid "“Siyā, sumane”ti bhagavā avoca:"
msgstr "“There would be, Sumanā,” said the Buddha."

msgctxt "an5.31:3.2"
msgid ""
"“yo so, sumane, dāyako so amuṃ adāyakaṃ devabhūto samāno pañcahi ṭhānehi "
"adhigaṇhāti—"
msgstr ""
"“As a god, the one who was a giver would surpass the other in five respects:"

msgctxt "an5.31:3.3"
msgid ""
"dibbena āyunā, dibbena vaṇṇena, dibbena sukhena, dibbena yasena, dibbena "
"ādhipateyyena."
msgstr "divine lifespan, beauty, happiness, fame, and dominion."

msgctxt "an5.31:3.4"
msgid ""
"Yo so, sumane, dāyako so amuṃ adāyakaṃ devabhūto samāno imehi pañcahi "
"ṭhānehi adhigaṇhāti”."
msgstr ""
"As a god, the one who was a giver would surpass the other in these five "
"respects.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an5.31:4.1"
msgid ""
"“Sace pana te, bhante, tato cutā itthattaṃ āgacchanti, manussabhūtānaṃ pana "
"nesaṃ, bhante, siyā viseso, siyā nānākaraṇan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But sir, if they pass away from there and come back to this state of "
"existence as human beings, would there still be any distinction or "
"difference between them?”"

msgctxt "an5.31:4.2"
msgid "“Siyā, sumane”ti bhagavā avoca:"
msgstr "“There would be, Sumanā,” said the Buddha."

msgctxt "an5.31:4.3"
msgid ""
"“yo so, sumane, dāyako so amuṃ adāyakaṃ manussabhūto samāno pañcahi ṭhānehi "
"adhigaṇhāti—"
msgstr ""
"“As a human being, the one who was a giver would surpass the other in five "
"respects:"

msgctxt "an5.31:4.4"
msgid ""
"mānusakena āyunā, mānusakena vaṇṇena, mānusakena sukhena, mānusakena yasena, "
"mānusakena ādhipateyyena."
msgstr "human lifespan, beauty, happiness, fame, and dominion."

msgctxt "an5.31:4.5"
msgid ""
"Yo so, sumane, dāyako so amuṃ adāyakaṃ manussabhūto samāno imehi pañcahi "
"ṭhānehi adhigaṇhāti”."
msgstr ""
"As a human being, the one who was a giver would surpass the other in these "
"five respects.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.34"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an5.31:5.1"
msgid ""
"“Sace pana te, bhante, ubho agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, pabbajitānaṃ "
"pana nesaṃ, bhante, siyā viseso, siyā nānākaraṇan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But sir, if they both go forth from the lay life to homelessness, would "
"there still be any distinction or difference between them?”"

msgctxt "an5.31:5.2"
msgid "“Siyā, sumane”ti bhagavā avoca:"
msgstr "“There would be, Sumanā,” said the Buddha."

msgctxt "an5.31:5.3"
msgid ""
"“yo so, sumane, dāyako so amuṃ adāyakaṃ pabbajito samāno pañcahi ṭhānehi "
"adhigaṇhāti—"
msgstr ""
"“As a renunciate, the one who was a giver would surpass the other in five "
"respects."

msgctxt "an5.31:5.4"
msgid ""
"yācitova bahulaṃ cīvaraṃ paribhuñjati appaṃ ayācito, yācitova bahulaṃ "
"piṇḍapātaṃ paribhuñjati appaṃ ayācito, yācitova bahulaṃ senāsanaṃ "
"paribhuñjati appaṃ ayācito, yācitova bahulaṃ "
"gilānapaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ paribhuñjati appaṃ ayācito."
msgstr ""
"They’d usually use only what they’ve been invited to accept—robes, alms-"
"food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick—rarely using them "
"without invitation."

msgctxt "an5.31:5.5"
msgid ""
"Yehi kho pana sabrahmacārīhi saddhiṃ viharati tyassa manāpeneva bahulaṃ "
"kāyakammena samudācaranti appaṃ amanāpena, manāpeneva bahulaṃ vacīkammena "
"samudācaranti appaṃ amanāpena, manāpeneva bahulaṃ manokammena samudācaranti "
"appaṃ amanāpena, manāpaṃyeva bahulaṃ upahāraṃ upaharanti appaṃ amanāpaṃ."
msgstr ""
"When living with other spiritual practitioners, they usually treat them "
"agreeably by way of body, speech, and mind, rarely disagreeably."

msgctxt "an5.31:5.6"
msgid ""
"Yo so, sumane, dāyako so amuṃ adāyakaṃ pabbajito samāno imehi pañcahi "
"ṭhānehi adhigaṇhātī”ti."
msgstr ""
"As a renunciate, the one who was a giver would surpass the other in these "
"five respects.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an5.31:6.1"
msgid ""
"“Sace pana te, bhante, ubho arahattaṃ pāpuṇanti, arahattappattānaṃ pana "
"nesaṃ, bhante, siyā viseso, siyā nānākaraṇan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But sir, if they both attain perfection, as perfected ones would there "
"still be any distinction or difference between them?”"

#. VAR: yadidaṃ vimuttiyā vimuttin”ti → vimuttanti (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an5.31:6.2"
msgid ""
"“Ettha kho panesāhaṃ, sumane, na kiñci nānākaraṇaṃ vadāmi, yadidaṃ vimuttiyā "
"vimuttin”ti."
msgstr ""
"“In that case, I say there is no difference between the freedom of one and "
"the freedom of the other.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an5.31:7.1"
msgid "“Acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante."
msgstr "“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing!"

msgctxt "an5.31:7.2"
msgid "Yāvañcidaṃ, bhante, alameva dānāni dātuṃ alaṃ puññāni kātuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"Just this much is quite enough to justify giving gifts and making merit."

msgctxt "an5.31:7.3"
msgid ""
"yatra hi nāma devabhūtassāpi upakārāni puññāni, manussabhūtassāpi upakārāni "
"puññāni, pabbajitassāpi upakārāni puññānī”ti."
msgstr ""
"For merit is helpful for those who have become gods, human beings, and "
"renunciates.”"

msgctxt "an5.31:7.4"
msgid "“Evametaṃ, sumane."
msgstr "“That’s so true, Sumanā."

msgctxt "an5.31:7.5"
msgid "Alañhi, sumane, dānāni dātuṃ alaṃ puññāni kātuṃ."
msgstr "It’s quite enough to justify giving gifts and making merit."

msgctxt "an5.31:7.6"
msgid ""
"Devabhūtassāpi upakārāni puññāni, manussabhūtassāpi upakārāni puññāni, "
"pabbajitassāpi upakārāni puññānī”ti."
msgstr ""
"For merit is helpful for those who have become gods, human beings, and "
"renunciates.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an5.31:8.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

#. VAR: Idaṃ vatvāna → idaṃ vatvā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.31:8.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an5.31:9.1"
msgid "“Yathāpi cando vimalo,"
msgstr "“The moon so immaculate,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.31:9.2"
msgid "gacchaṃ ākāsadhātuyā;"
msgstr "journeying across the dimension of space;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.31:9.3"
msgid "Sabbe tārāgaṇe loke,"
msgstr "outshines with its radiance"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.31:9.4"
msgid "ābhāya atirocati."
msgstr "all the world’s stars."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an5.31:10.1"
msgid "Tatheva sīlasampanno,"
msgstr "So too, a faithful individual,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.31:10.2"
msgid "saddho purisapuggalo;"
msgstr "perfect in ethics,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.31:10.3"
msgid "Sabbe maccharino loke,"
msgstr "outshines with their generosity"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.31:10.4"
msgid "cāgena atirocati."
msgstr "all the world’s stingy people."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an5.31:11.1"
msgid "Yathāpi megho thanayaṃ,"
msgstr "The thundering rain cloud,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.31:11.2"
msgid "vijjumālī satakkaku;"
msgstr "its hundred peaks wreathed in lightning,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.31:11.3"
msgid "Thalaṃ ninnañca pūreti,"
msgstr "pours down over the rich earth,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.31:11.4"
msgid "abhivassaṃ vasundharaṃ."
msgstr "soaking the plains and lowlands."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an5.31:12.1"
msgid "Evaṃ dassanasampanno,"
msgstr "Even so, an astute person accomplished in vision,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.31:12.2"
msgid "sammāsambuddhasāvako;"
msgstr "a disciple of the fully awakened Buddha,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.31:12.3"
msgid "Macchariṃ adhigaṇhāti,"
msgstr "surpasses a mean person"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.31:12.4"
msgid "pañcaṭhānehi paṇḍito."
msgstr "in five respects:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
#. VAR: yasasā ceva → āyunā ca yasena ca (mr)
msgctxt "an5.31:13.1"
msgid "Āyunā yasasā ceva,"
msgstr "long life and fame,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.31:13.2"
msgid "vaṇṇena ca sukhena ca;"
msgstr "beauty and happiness."

#. <br>
#. VAR: bhogaparibyūḷho → bhogaparibbūḷho (bj, pts1) | bhogaparibyuḷho (s1-3)
msgctxt "an5.31:13.3"
msgid "Sa ve bhogaparibyūḷho,"
msgstr "Blessed with riches,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.31:13.4"
msgid "pecca sagge pamodatī”ti."
msgstr "they depart to rejoice in heaven.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.31:13.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
